                <head type="title">Grace Allen (<!--Entry needed here.-->)</head>
                <p>Eldest daughter<!--Correction needed here.--> of George Allen. In 1901, along with her brothers Hugh Allen
                    and William Allen, she became a member of the board of the publishing business
                    now named George Allen and Sons. Grace had an important role in preparing many
                    of her father&#x02BC;s late&#x2010;century publications of
                    Ruskin&#x02BC;s early works. W. G. Collingwood says in <hi rend="italic"
                        >Poems</hi> ([1891], 1:268) that she transcribed poems for that edition from
                    her father&#x02BC;s copy of the scarce <hi rend="italic">Poems</hi>
                    (1850).</p>
                <p>See Dawson, <hi rend="italic">People&#x2019;s Ruskin</hi>, 10.</p>
            </div>
